⚠️ **IMPORTANT: Socket.IO + Vercel Limitation** ⚠️

This project uses Socket.IO with a custom server, which **WILL NOT work on Vercel**.

While the build may succeed by copying routes-manifest.json, the **real-time chat functionality will be broken** because:

1. Vercel uses serverless functions - no persistent connections
2. Socket.IO requires a long-running server process
3. WebSocket connections will fail

## ✅ Working Deployment Options:

### **Railway** (Recommended)
- Full Socket.IO support
- Free tier available
- 1-click GitHub deployment
- Visit: https://railway.app

### **Render**
- WebSocket support
- Free tier
- GitHub integration
- Visit: https://render.com

### **DigitalOcean App Platform**
- Full server support
- Predictable pricing
- Visit: https://www.digitalocean.com/products/app-platform

## 📖 Full Instructions
See `DEPLOYMENT.md` for complete step-by-step deployment guide.

---

**If you must use Vercel**, you would need to:
1. Remove the custom Socket.IO server
2. Use a separate WebSocket service (like Pusher or Ably)
3. Significantly refactor the application

**Recommendation: Deploy to Railway instead - it works perfectly with Socket.IO!**
